          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2015-06-15T21:03:12Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Next Generation Electric Systems Act </b></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Energy (DOE) to establish a grants program for eligible partnerships to develop and implement projects related to achieving the transformation of the future electric grid by the year 2030 using a comprehensive approach to electric system design and architecture. </p> <p>Eligible partnerships may include any institution of higher education, National Laboratory, representative of a state or local government, representative of an Indian tribe, federal power marketing administration, industry expert, or nonprofit industry trade association, but must include at least one electric utility (either investor-owned or publicly owned), technology provider, rural electric cooperative, Regional Transmission Organization, or Independent System Operator.</p> <p>DOE must, when selecting eligible partnerships to receive grants, give priority to those proposing projects for which a cost-share is to be provided. </p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2015-05-06T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
